<font color="#FF0000">ED &amp; COOK AT THE SUPER BOWL</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan 24 17:28:32 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Cook was sitting in the upper rows of the stadium watching the Super Bowl and noticed an empty seat in the third row on the fifty yard line.Ā <br>
After the second quarter had begun, he noticed the seat was still empty and approached the man. <br><br>
He noticed that it was MTF and asked if anyone was sitting there. MTF said no and that he was welcome to sit there.ĀĀ<br><br>
Cook began talking to Ed and asked if he knew who the seat belonged to.Ā <br><br>
&quot;Yes, Ed answered.Ā This seat has belonged to my ex-wife for the last ten years but she passed away.&quot;<br><br>
Noting what a kind man Ed was, Cook knew he had great friends like Gary,Tom, SW, LBW, Paul, Art, John, Doc Dell and others, so Cook asked if there wasn't a friend or relative he might have asked to come to the game with<br>
him, Ed answered, <br>
&quot;Yes, but they're all at the funeral.&quot;<br>

